satkit-data — licensing and data provenance
============================================

PACKAGING
---------
The satkit-data packaging — the `satkit_data` Python wrapper, its layout,
and the conda recipe — is the only original, copyrightable contribution in
this distribution and is made available by Steven Michael under your choice
of the MIT License OR the Apache License, Version 2.0.

    Copyright (c) Steven Michael

    MIT: https://opensource.org/license/mit
    Apache-2.0: https://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0

BUNDLED DATA FILES
------------------
The data files shipped in `satkit_data/data/` are third-party scientific
reference data, redistributed unmodified. They are not the work of the
packager. Each is a public-domain U.S. Government work or is otherwise made
freely available for redistribution and scientific use by its producer.
Provenance and terms for each:

  lnxp1900p2053.421
    JPL Development Ephemeris DE421 (planetary/lunar ephemeris).
    Producer: NASA Jet Propulsion Laboratory.
    Terms: U.S. Government work, public domain (17 U.S.C. §105); freely
    redistributable. Source: https://ssd.jpl.nasa.gov/

  EGM96.gfc
    Earth Gravitational Model 1996 (spherical-harmonic coefficients).
    Producer: NASA GSFC / NIMA (now NGA) / Ohio State University.
    Terms: U.S. Government work, public domain; distributed via ICGEM.

  JGM2.gfc, JGM3.gfc
    Joint Gravity Model 2/3.
    Producer: NASA GSFC / University of Texas Center for Space Research.
    Terms: U.S. Government work, public domain; freely available.

  ITU_GRACE16.gfc
    ITU_GRACE16 GRACE-derived gravity field model.
    Producer: Istanbul Technical University; distributed via ICGEM
    (GFZ Potsdam). Terms: freely available for scientific use;
    attribution to the model authors requested.

  tab5.2a.txt, tab5.2b.txt, tab5.2d.txt
    IERS Conventions (2010), Technical Note 36 precession-nutation series.
    Producer: International Earth Rotation and Reference Systems Service.
    Terms: freely available for scientific use. Source: https://www.iers.org/

  leap-seconds.list
    Historical TAI−UTC leap-second table.
    Producer: IERS / IETF (per the file's own usage statement).
    Terms: freely redistributable.

  msis21.parm
    NRLMSIS 2.1 empirical atmospheric model parameters.
    Producer: U.S. Naval Research Laboratory.
    Terms: U.S. Government work; NRLMSIS 2.x is released for open use.
    Source: https://map.nrl.navy.mil/

Note: Earth orientation parameters (EOP-All.csv) and space weather
(SW-All.csv) are deliberately NOT bundled — they are regenerated daily by
CelesTrak and are fetched on demand by satkit at runtime.

If you are a rights holder for any bundled file and believe its terms are
misstated here, please open an issue at
https://github.com/ssmichael1/satkit and it will be corrected.
